<div class="recording-notice" data-component="RecordingNotice">
  <p>
    This vehicle may use fixed audio and video recording equipment that
    captures the driver, the passenger compartment, and the area around the
    vehicle.
  </p>

  <p>
    Recording is used for driver safety, passenger safety, trip documentation,
    incident review, and security. Some rides may also be livestreamed or
    later included in public content when the stream setup is active.
  </p>

  <p>
    By entering or remaining in the vehicle after this notice is visible, you
    acknowledge that audio and video recording may occur. If you do not want
    to be recorded or streamed, tell me before the ride begins. Depending on
    the situation, I may stop a public stream, avoid using the footage,
    decline a direct booking, or ask that the trip be handled another way.
    Safety recording may remain active.
  </p>

  <p>
    Please do not discuss private, confidential, medical, financial, legal,
    employment, family, address, or other sensitive information in the
    vehicle if you do not want it captured.
  </p>

  <p>
    I do not intentionally publish private passenger information. I may mute,
    delete, blur, remove, or refuse to publish material that exposes private
    facts, creates a safety issue, identifies a passenger unnecessarily, or
    crosses a line.
  </p>

  <p>
    Retention: raw recordings are kept on local storage for about 30 days for
    incident review, then deleted. Material posted on Twitch typically stays
    available for about 14 days before rotating off.
  </p>

  <p class="footnote">
    This notice is written for Missouri rides. Other states may have
    different recording and consent rules.
  </p>
</div>

<style>
  .recording-notice p {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    font-size: 14.5px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--fg-dim);
  }

  .recording-notice .footnote {
    margin: 22px 0 0;
    padding-top: 14px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--fg-mute);
  }
</style>
